Defensive Stance	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.DwarvenDefenderClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When he needs to, a defender can become a stalwart bastion of defense. In this defensive stance, a defender gains phenomenal strength and durability, but he cannot move from the spot he is defending. He gains +2 to Strength, +4 to Constitution, a +2 resistance bonus on all saves, and a +4 dodge bonus to AC. The increase in Constitution increases the defender's hit points by 2 points per level, but these hit points go away at the end of the defensive stance when the Constitution score drops back 4 points. These extra hit points are not lost first the way temporary hit points are. While in a defensive stance, a defender cannot use skills or abilities that would require him to shift his position, such as Move Silently or Jump. A defensive stance lasts for a number of rounds equal to 3 + the character's (newly improved) Constitution modifier. A defender may end his defensive stance voluntarily prior to this limit. At the end of the defensive stance, the defender is winded and takes a -2 penalty to Strength for the duration of that encounter. A defender can only use his defensive stance a certain number of times per day as determined by his level (see Table 6-9). Using the defensive stance takes no time itself, but a defender can only do so during his action. (A defender can't, for example, use the stance when struck down by an arrow in order to get the extra hit points from the increased Constitution.)	KEY:Dwarven Defender ~ Defensive Stance				DEFINE:DwarvenDefenderDefensiveStanceTimes|0	DEFINE:DwarvenDefenderDefensiveStanceLVL|0				BONUS:VAR|DefensiveStanceTimes|(DwarvenDefenderDefensiveStanceLVL+1)/2	BONUS:VAR|DwarvenDefenderDefensiveStanceLVL|DwarvenDefenderLVL								ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Defensive Stance								SORTKEY:Class_Dwarven_Defender	SOURCEPAGE:DMG	
Uncanny Dodge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.DwarvenDefenderClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Uncanny Dodge	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Starting at 2nd level, a dwarven defender gains the extraordinary ability to react to danger before his senses would normally allow him to even be aware of it. At 2nd level and above, he retains his Dexterity bonus to AC (if any) regardless of being caught flat-footed or struck by an invisible attacker. (He still loses any Dexterity bonus to AC if immobilized.) If a character gains uncanny dodge from a second class (such as rogue), the character automatically gains improved uncanny dodge (see below).	KEY:Dwarven Defender ~ Uncanny Dodge									BONUS:VAR|UncannyDodgeFlankingLevel|DwarvenDefenderLVL|TYPE=EachClass.REPLACE																	SORTKEY:Class_Dwarven_Defender	SOURCEPAGE:DMG	
Trap Sense	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.DwarvenDefenderClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 4th level, a dwarven defender gains an intuitive sense that alerts him to danger from traps, giving him a +1 bonus on Reflex saves made to avoid traps and a +1 dodge bonus to AC against attacks by traps. At 8th level, these bonuses rise to +2. These bonuses stack with trap sense bonuses gained from other classes.	KEY:Dwarven Defender ~ Trap Sense				DEFINE:DwarvenDefenderTrapSense|0					BONUS:VAR|TrapSenseBonus|DwarvenDefenderLVL/4									ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Trap Sense								SORTKEY:Class_Dwarven_Defender	SOURCEPAGE:DMG	
